                                     Tricky interview questions
1. Can you overload a method by changing only the return type?
No, overloading requires a different method signature, which includes the number or type of parameters.
2. Can you override a static method?
No, static methods belong to the class, not the instance, so they cannot be overridden.
3. What happens if you try to override a method without using the @Override annotation?
The code will still compile and run, but you may not get the intended behavior if you accidentally
change the method signature. The @Override annotation helps catch such mistakes at compile time.
4. Can you overload a method with varargs?
Yes, you can overload a method with varargs, but the varargs method must have a different parameter list than the other overloaded methods.
5. Can you override a method and change its access modifier?
Yes, you can override a method and change its access modifier, but the new access level cannot

